{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"16536","heading":"Protecting America’s Competitive Edge (PACE) graduate fellowship program","label":"16536 Protecting America’s Competitive Edge (PACE) graduate fellowship program","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch149/schXVII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2011—Subsec. (f)(4) to (6). added pars. (4) to (6).Pub. L. 111–358"],"amendments":["Amendments2011—Subsec. (f)(4) to (6). added pars. (4) to (6).Pub. L. 111–358"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Definition of eligible student","label":"a Definition of eligible student","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In this section, the term “eligible student” means a student who attends an institution of higher education that offers a doctoral degree in a field relevant to a mission area of the Department.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Establishment","label":"b Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall establish a graduate fellowship program for eligible students pursuing a doctoral degree in a mission area of the Department.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Selection","label":"c Selection","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary shall award fellowships to eligible students under this section through a competitive merit review process, involving written and oral interviews, that will result in a wide distribution of awards throughout the United States, as determined by the Secretary.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Criteria","label":"2 Criteria","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to pursue a field of science or engineering of importance to a mission area of the Department;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fc%2F2%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the capacity of the eligible student to understand technical topics relating to the fellowship that can be derived from the first principles of the technical topics;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fc%2F2%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"imagination and creativity;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/B/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fc%2F2%2FB%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"leadership skills in organizations or intellectual endeavors, demonstrated through awards and past experience; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/B/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fc%2F2%2FB%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"excellent verbal and communication skills to explain, defend, and demonstrate an understanding of technical subjects relating to the fellowship; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fc%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"to be a citizen or legal permanent resident of the United States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Awards","label":"d Awards","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Amount","label":"1 Amount","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fd%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"provide an annual living stipend; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fd%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/1/B/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"graduate tuition at an institution of higher education described in subsection (a); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/1/B/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/1/B","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fd%2F1%2FB%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"incidental expenses associated with curricula and research at the institution of higher education (including books, computers, and software).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Duration","label":"2 Duration","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A fellowship awarded under this section shall be up to 3 years duration within a 5-year period.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Portability","label":"3 Portability","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fd%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A fellowship awarded under this section shall be portable with the eligible student.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Administration","label":"e Administration","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/e/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fe%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"shall administer the program established under this section; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/e/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/e","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Fe%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"may enter into a contract with a nonprofit entity to administer the program, including the selection and award of fellowships.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Authorization of appropriations","label":"f Authorization of appropriations","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Ff%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"$7,500,000 for fiscal year 2008;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Ff%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"$12,000,000 for fiscal year 2009, including nonexpiring fellowships for the preceding fiscal year;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Ff%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"$20,000,000 for fiscal year 2010, including nonexpiring fellowships for preceding fiscal years;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Ff%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"$20,600,000 for fiscal year 2011;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Ff%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"$21,200,000 for fiscal year 2012; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s16536/f","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs16536%2Ff%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"$21,900,000 for fiscal year 2013.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
